summary: This is an email from January 27, 2021, forwarding attachments including meeting notes, business cards, and a legal memo in support of a motion to suppress evidence obtained from a subpoena to BSF. It appears to be legal correspondence related to a motion in the Epstein case, sent to or from the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York.
keyFacts: An email dated January 27, 2021, forwards legal documents related to the Epstein case.
Attachments include meeting notes, business cards, and a legal memo supporting a motion to suppress evidence.
The motion seeks to suppress evidence obtained from a subpoena to an entity referred to as 'BSF'.
The correspondence involves the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York.
The document reference 'EFTA00019070' is part of a larger data set (Set 8) of released documents.
